{"title_page": "Curfews and lockdowns related to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic", "text_new": "{{short description|Details of restrictions imposed due to COVID-19}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic sidebar|expanded=international}}\n\nThis list of '''COVID-19 related curfews and lockdowns''' shows worldwide [[curfew]]s and similar restrictions (known as [[stay-at-home order]]s, shelter-in-place orders, [[Shutdown (economics)|shutdowns]]/[[lockdown]]s) related to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] and established to prevent further spread of the [[severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2]] (SARS-CoV-2), which causes [[coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]].\n\nThe pandemic has resulted in the largest amount of shutdowns/lockdowns worldwide at the same time in [[history]].{{cn|date=April 2020}} Curfews and lockdowns between and within nations are of varying stringency.\n\n==Current lockdowns==\n\n<div style=\"float:left;\">{{2020 coronavirus quarantines outside Hubei}}</div>\n\n<div style=\"float:right;\">\n[[File:Joint inspection by police and army in Malaysia during MCO.jpg|thumb|Joint inspection by the [[Royal Malaysia Police|police]] and [[Malaysian Army|army]] during the enhanced [[2020 Malaysia movement control order|movement control order]] in Malaysia.]]\n[[File:CRPF trooper during Curfew.png|thumb|Officer of the [[Central Armed Police Forces]] during national COVID-19 curfew in India.]]\n[[File:High Street and Curfew Tower, Cushendall, Co. Antrim - geograph.org.uk - 1381257.jpg|thumb|Empty street in Cushendall, [[Northern Ireland]]]]\n[[File:6954Baliuag enhanced community quarantine 37.jpg|thumb|2020 [[Curfew Pass]] in Baliuag, Phillippines.]]\n[[File:Mahane Yehuda Market closed in coronavirus outbreak.jpg|thumb|Mahane Yehuda Market in Jerusalem.]]\n[[File:Policemen wearing masks patrolling Wuhan Tianhe Airport during Wuhan coronavirus outbreak.jpg|thumb|Policemen wearing masks patrolling Wuhan Tianhe Airport during Wuhan coronavirus outbreak (22 January 2020)]]\n[[File:Playground, Eckernf\u00f6rde (P1100616).jpg|thumb|closed-off public playground in northern Germany]]\n</div>\n\n{{clear}}\n\n==Type of regulation by country==\n\n{{2020 coronavirus pandemic curfews}}\n{{clear}}\n\n==Countries and dependent territories that have not issued curfews or lockdowns==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable style=\"font-size:80%;\"\n|-\n|{{NIC}} || [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Nicaragua]] || <ref>https://foreignpolicy.com/2020/04/17/ortega-virus-murillo-nicaragua-is-stumbling-into-coronavirus-disaster/</ref>\n|-\n|{{SWE}} || [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Sweden]] || <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rt.com/news/484515-sweden-covid-no-lockdown/|title=Sweden says no to quarantine \u2013 is this the most reckless or the most proportionate Covid-19 response in the West?|website=RT International|language=en|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{TKM}} || [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Turkmenistan]] || <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://rsf.org/en/news/coronavirus-limits-turkmenistan|title=Coronavirus off limits in Turkmenistan {{!}} Reporters without borders|date=2020-03-31|website=RSF|language=en|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==China==\nDue to the pandemic originating in China, it was the first country to enforce lockdowns in its various regions starting in January. By early April, all lockdowns had ended or relaxed to a certain degree as the cases started to dwindle and the outbreak had come under control.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.express.co.uk/travel/articles/1257717/china-lockdown-how-long-was-china-lockdown-timeframe-wuhan|title=China lockdown: How long was China on lockdown?|last=Langton|first=Kaisha|date=20 April 2020|website=Daily Express|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=21 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.businessinsider.com/china-lockdowns-reimposed-fear-second-coronavirus-wave-wuhan-hubei-2020-4|title=China is trying to relax its severe coronavirus lockdown, but a series of forced re-closures shows how hard it is to get back to normal|last=Bostock|first=Bill|date=6 April 2020|website=Business Insider|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=21 April 2020}}</ref>\n<div style=\"float:left;\">{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic lockdowns in mainland China}}</div>\n<div style=\"clear:both;\"></div>\n\n==See also==\n{{commonscat|COVID-19 pandemic quarantine}}\n*[[National responses to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n*[[Social distancing measures related to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n*[[Timeline of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n*[[Travel restrictions related to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n*[[Preventive action]] (lockdown)\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n{{2019\u201320_coronavirus_pandemic}}\n\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic-related lists]]\n[[Category:Containment efforts related to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic| ]]\n[[Category:Curfews]]\n[[Category:Emergency management]]\n[[Category:Country lockdowns]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Details of restrictions imposed due to COVID-19}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic sidebar|expanded=international}}\n\nThis list of '''COVID-19 related curfews and lockdowns''' shows worldwide [[curfew]]s and similar restrictions (known as [[stay-at-home order]]s, shelter-in-place orders, [[Shutdown (economics)|shutdowns]]/[[lockdown]]s) related to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] and established to prevent further spread of the [[severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2]] (SARS-CoV-2), which causes [[coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]].\n\nThe pandemic has resulted in the largest amount of shutdowns/lockdowns worldwide at the same time in [[history]].{{cn|date=April 2020}} Curfews and lockdowns between and within nations are of varying stringency.\n\n==Current lockdowns==\n<div style=\"float:left;\">{{2020 coronavirus quarantines outside Hubei}}</div>\n{{clear}}\n\n[[File:Joint inspection by police and army in Malaysia during MCO.jpg|thumb|Joint inspection by the [[Royal Malaysia Police|police]] and [[Malaysian Army|army]] during the enhanced [[2020 Malaysia movement control order|movement control order]] in Malaysia.]]\n[[File:CRPF trooper during Curfew.png|thumb|Officer of the [[Central Armed Police Forces]] during national COVID-19 curfew in India.]]\n[[File:High Street and Curfew Tower, Cushendall, Co. Antrim - geograph.org.uk - 1381257.jpg|thumb|Empty street in Cushendall, [[Northern Ireland]]]]\n[[File:6954Baliuag enhanced community quarantine 37.jpg|thumb|2020 [[Curfew Pass]] in Baliuag, Phillippines.]]\n[[File:Mahane Yehuda Market closed in coronavirus outbreak.jpg|thumb|Mahane Yehuda Market in Jerusalem.]]\n[[File:Policemen wearing masks patrolling Wuhan Tianhe Airport during Wuhan coronavirus outbreak.jpg|thumb|Policemen wearing masks patrolling Wuhan Tianhe Airport during Wuhan coronavirus outbreak (22 January 2020)]]\n[[File:Playground, Eckernf\u00f6rde (P1100616).jpg|thumb|closed-off public playground in northern Germany]]\n==Type of regulation by country==\n\n{{2020 coronavirus pandemic curfews}}\n{{clear}}\n\n==Countries and dependent territories that have not issued curfews or lockdowns==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable style=\"font-size:80%;\"\n|-\n|{{NIC}} || [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Nicaragua]] || <ref>https://foreignpolicy.com/2020/04/17/ortega-virus-murillo-nicaragua-is-stumbling-into-coronavirus-disaster/</ref>\n|-\n|{{SWE}} || [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Sweden]] || <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rt.com/news/484515-sweden-covid-no-lockdown/|title=Sweden says no to quarantine \u2013 is this the most reckless or the most proportionate Covid-19 response in the West?|website=RT International|language=en|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{TKM}} || [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Turkmenistan]] || <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://rsf.org/en/news/coronavirus-limits-turkmenistan|title=Coronavirus off limits in Turkmenistan {{!}} Reporters without borders|date=2020-03-31|website=RSF|language=en|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==China==\nDue to the pandemic originating in China, it was the first country to enforce lockdowns in its various regions starting in January. By early April, all lockdowns had ended or relaxed to a certain degree as the cases started to dwindle and the outbreak had come under control.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.express.co.uk/travel/articles/1257717/china-lockdown-how-long-was-china-lockdown-timeframe-wuhan|title=China lockdown: How long was China on lockdown?|last=Langton|first=Kaisha|date=20 April 2020|website=Daily Express|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=21 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.businessinsider.com/china-lockdowns-reimposed-fear-second-coronavirus-wave-wuhan-hubei-2020-4|title=China is trying to relax its severe coronavirus lockdown, but a series of forced re-closures shows how hard it is to get back to normal|last=Bostock|first=Bill|date=6 April 2020|website=Business Insider|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=21 April 2020}}</ref>\n<div style=\"float:left;\">{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic lockdowns in mainland China}}</div>\n<div style=\"clear:both;\"></div>\n\n==See also==\n{{commonscat|COVID-19 pandemic quarantine}}\n*[[National responses to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n*[[Social distancing measures related to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n*[[Timeline of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n*[[Travel restrictions related to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n*[[Preventive action]] (lockdown)\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n{{2019\u201320_coronavirus_pandemic}}\n\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic-related lists]]\n[[Category:Containment efforts related to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pan